CCCCTTAAIILL -- Environmental Variable

Append options to end of cc command line
eexxppoorrtt CCCCTTAAIILL=_o_p_t_i_o_n_s

The  COHERENT compiler  cccc  reads the  environmental  variables CCCCHHEEAADD  and
CCCCTTAAIILL before it begins its work.   You can set these variables to hold the
default options that you want the compiler always to use.

cccc appends the options in CCCCTTAAIILL to the end of its command line.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
cccc, CCCCHHEEAADD, eennvviirroonnmmeennttaall vvaarriiaabblleess
